Port St John s municipal bosses are pumping millions of rands into fixing access roads, some to tourism hotspots, as a way to boost the economy of the Wild Coast s crown jewel . Mayor Lindelwa Rolobile told the Daily Dispatch yesterday that nearly R35-million of their total R234-million capital budget for the 2017-18 financial year had been allocated towards revamping several access roads.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.